image.altText: A close up of Greg Lynn standing in front of a body of water near some rocks.

props.synopsis: Greg Lynn has taken the stand before a Supreme Court jury as he fights two murder charges over the deaths of missing campers Carol Clay and Russell Hill.

title.children: Greg Lynn apologises to families of Victorian campers as he gives evidence in murder trial

image.altText: A close shot of Brereton, who is sitting in the offices of the new national anti--corruption commission

props.synopsis: The National Anti-Corruption Commission (NACC) has announced it will not pursue fresh corruption investigations into six public officials involved in the robodebt scandal.

title.children: Anti-corruption watchdog decides not to pursue Robodebt corruption investigation

image.altText: Current treasurer Jim Chalmers (left) and former treasurer Paul Keating (right).

props.synopsis: Jim Chalmers is the same age as Paul Keating was when he declared Australia was in "the recession we had to have". Is he doomed to tread the same path?

title.children: Australia's economy is beginning to look a lot like 1990. But there's one key difference

image.altText: AFL footballer celebrates a goal

props.synopsis: Adem Yze's young Tigers have found their roar once more, travelling to Adelaide on a five-day back-up to down the Crows by eight points in a thriller.

title.children: Tigers upset Crows in thrilling clash to record second win of the season in emphatic fashion

image.altText: Man holding diet book.

props.synopsis: British TV doctor Michael Mosley has been reported missing after going on a coastal walk alone on the Greek island of Symi.

title.children: British TV doctor Michael Mosley missing in Greece after lone coastal walk

image.altText: Aerial shot of dozens of houses in neat rows in a new outer-suburban housing estate.

props.synopsis: Industry experts say it's not time to ring the alarm bells over low building approval numbers, but the federal government's plan for 1.2 million homes by 2029 is definitely ambitious.

title.children: The latest building stats are in — here's what they say about the future of the housing crisis

image.altText: A man outside a hospital.

props.synopsis: Bendigo Health remains in a code yellow internal emergency after it couldn't keep up with the number of people attending for treatment, with workers saying Victoria's health system is "struggling", "unprepared", and needs "rebuilding".

title.children: Burnt-out nurses at Victorian hospital say government needs to rebuild broken health system

image.altText: Officer Cadets on parade at ADFA.

props.synopsis: Military data has revealed more than a third of female recruits reported sexual misconduct while attending the Australian Defence Force Academy in Canberra.

title.children: More than a third of female defence academy recruits report sexual misconduct

image.altText: A man in a suit with grey hair leans back and gestures as he speaks on a stage.

props.synopsis: Nine Entertainment chairman Peter Costello denies assaulting a journalist at Canberra Airport after The Australian posted footage that appears to show Mr Costello walking towards reporter Liam Mendes, who was asking him questions, before Mr Mendes falls backwards.

title.children: Nine chairman Peter Costello denies assaulting journalist at Canberra Airport

image.altText: Smoke plumes coming out from underneath a rocket.

props.synopsis: SpaceX's Starship rocket, designed to eventually send astronauts to the Moon and beyond, has undergone its fourth flight test.

title.children: SpaceX successfully launches Starship rocket to space on fourth test flight, survives re-entry which blew up last flight

image.altText: Joe Biden and Emmanuel Macron on D-Day in Normandy.

props.synopsis: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy were among state heads who travelled to northern France to commemorate the 80th anniversary of D-Day.

title.children: World leaders come together on beaches of Normandy to commemorate D-Day

image.altText: A gas stove.

props.synopsis: The Victorian government has approved an application for a project to extract gas offshore near Port Campbell, on the Great Ocean Road. It's the first application to be made since 2014.

title.children: Victoria grants first gas extraction licence in 10 years in the state's south-west

image.altText: A woman with curly blonde hair and her adult son.

props.synopsis: Jeremy Adlam is receiving palliative care on his mum's farm, but organising it proved difficult. Experts say it's a problem that needs to be addressed now.

title.children: Demand for palliative care is tipped to double and experts say Jeremy's struggle must be taken as a warning

image.altText: Paige Hadley and Jamie-Lee Price hug a smiling Matilda Garrett

props.synopsis: Cash-strapped Netball Australia has been offered a fresh financial lifeline just weeks after the sport's governing body appointed Diamonds star Liz Ellis to its board.

title.children: Cash-strapped Netball Australia to receive funding, less than half of what was promised

image.altText: A boy looks amid grey rubble

props.synopsis: The Israeli military says Hamas militants were operating from within the Nuseirat school, while witnesses recount chaotic scenes as the injured are rushed to nearby hospitals.

title.children: Israeli strike kills at least 33 people at Gaza school that military claims was being used by Hamas

image.altText: Isabel Walker Life Chances 2

props.synopsis: A long-term study of the lives of 167 babies can tell us a lot about how family bonds, wealth, education and changes to our social safety net can impact a person's life.

title.children: Destiny's children: The 167 babies researchers say show us the importance of family above finances

image.altText: A group of forensics police officers wearing blue overalls outside a home on a suburban street.

props.synopsis: A scathing report identified more than 170 breaches of the NSW Police Force's own domestic violence procedures, with officers failing to do the basics like seizing guns, taking a statement, or checking CCTV footage.

title.children: 'Inexcusable failure': Damning report on one police force reflects the failures of another

image.altText: Aerial shot of the Icon of the Seas, with a tangle of colourful waterslides at the back.

props.synopsis: Jane Newson saves for a P&O cruise every year and says it's her chance to see the world when other options are too expensive. The cruise company's surprise exit from Australia after 90 years is the end of an era for her and the national icon.

title.children: P&O exiting Australia is the end of a cruising era — and 'mega ships' could be to blame

image.altText: Close up of Putin in a suit

props.synopsis: Russia could arm countries with long-range weapons to strike Western targets in response to NATO allies allowing Ukraine to use their arms to attack Russian territory, President Vladimir Putin warns.

title.children: Putin warns Russia could provide weapons to strike Western targets

image.altText: Greens leader Adam Bandt holds his arms out wide while speaking with Anthony Albanese in the House of Representatives

props.synopsis: It might have felt good to land a few punches on the Greens, but in winning that parliamentary battle some in Labor fear they could lose the war in key seats at the next election.

title.children: In teaming up with the Liberals against the Greens, Labor may have won the battle but lost the war

image.altText: A large crowd of people, including many waving Israeli flags, outside a large building.

props.synopsis: Violence has erupted at Israel's annual Jerusalem Day march, with some Jewish Israelis attacking Palestinians and journalists, including an ABC News team, while chanting offensive slogans.

title.children: Palestinians, journalists attacked as crowds chant 'Death to Arabs' at Israel's annual Jerusalem Day march

image.altText: A young man wearing a baseball cap looks down at his phone

props.synopsis: A man accused of murdering 15-year-old Cassius Turvey, Jack Brearley, will be applying for a separate trial on charges of detaining and assaulting another teenager in the days before the alleged attack on the Perth schoolboy.

title.children: One of Cassius Turvey's accused murderers wants separate trial for second alleged attack

image.altText: Protesters sit down and chant at the Australian National University pro-Palestine encampment.

props.synopsis: The ABC confirms a student has been expelled after making comments about Hamas on ABC radio in April.

title.children: ANU expels pro-Palestinian student after comments made on air stating Hamas deserves 'unconditional support'

image.altText: A photo of Daryl, Jacki, John and Ossie all smiling at the camera.

props.synopsis: Reflecting on how TV has evolved since the demise of the variety genre on Australian screens — and that's not necessarily a bad thing.

title.children: The daggy humour of Hey Hey made cruel jokes permissible in the mainstream. Thankfully TV has evolved

image.altText: tinned peaches on a supermarket shelf

props.synopsis: One of Australia’s largest food processors says it has reacted to shoppers buying cheaper imported food amid the cost-of-living crisis.

title.children: Fruit growers urge shoppers to buy local after major processor SPC cuts canned fruit production

image.altText: Two swans in a lake

props.synopsis: A nearly two-decade study of birds living in Melbourne's Albert Park has revealed surprising relationship patterns between black swans.

title.children: A successful monogamous relationship could involve month-long breaks — according to swans

image.altText: Selwyn Cobbo high-fives Queensland Maroons teammate Hamiso Tabuai-Fidow during State of Origin I.

props.synopsis: Naming Selwyn Cobbo on the bench for State of Origin I could have been disastrous for Billy Slater and Queensland, but it ultimately paid off in the most predictable way imaginable.

title.children: 'Hindsight's a great thing': Slater's big bench gamble proves to not be a gamble at all in Origin I

image.altText: Farmers standing in shed.

props.synopsis: Wheatbelt farmers like Kristin Lefroy are sitting on a secure water supply despite having endured a bone-dry summer and autumn. They say adopting desalination has been the key.

title.children: Five years ago these farmers' salty wells were useless. Now they are a source of pure water when it is needed most

image.altText: Lightning appears amid a storm as Mount Ibu spews volcanic material during an eruption, as seen from Gam Ici in West Halmahera,

props.synopsis: Indonesia's Mount Ibu volcano erupts twice in the same day, firing bright red lava and rocks into the night sky, triggering a spectacular display of volcanic lightning.

title.children: Indonesia's Mount Ibu volcano erupts twice in one day, spewing red-hot lava and triggering lightning

image.altText: Hunter Biden, wearing a suit and US flag pin, and Melissa Cohen Biden, wearing sunglasses and a black top.

props.synopsis: Hunter Biden's ex-wife and a former girlfriend testify about finding his crack pipes, and jurors are shown photos of him bare-chested in a bubble bath and told about his visit to a strip club.

title.children: Hunter Biden's exes give evidence as president's son's trial probes his personal life

image.altText: A composite image showing a shark and an echidna, both swimming in the ocean.

props.synopsis: Nicholas Lubitz witnessed the remarkable emetic incident during a three-year project that saw hundreds of marine creatures tagged off the Queensland coast.

title.children: 'Wasn't quite sitting right': Scientist shocked by sight of shark vomiting up echidna

image.altText: Collage of Julie Inman Grant and Elon Musk with a vs slash between them in the style of Street Fighter video game.

props.synopsis: Most of the country has bought cheap tickets to the hotly-anticipated action blockbuster, eSafety v Elon Musk, filmed on location at the Australian Federal Court.

title.children: What, did you think the battle between eSafety and X was over? Sit down. We're not even halfway

image.altText: A white and black dog trying to poke its head out of a cat flap

props.synopsis: A cat stuck in a hole, a dog who looks like his owner, and a Tarzan flying cat are among the winners of the 2024 Comedy Pet Photo Awards.

title.children: Hector the dog trying to squeeze through a tiny cat flap wins funniest pet photo of the year
